original: Kanada, Japan, Kina o. Indien 21-23. Kapt. i Värml. reg. res. 46. Inneh. av grosshand:firman F. E. Karlström i Amål ’Samt minutaffär, i Åmål, Säff-le o. Årjäng. Led. av stadsfullm. (h) sed. 37, v. ordf. i beredn :utsk. o. led. av flera nd!r. Ordf. i Åmiåls köpm:-fören., v. ordf. i Värml.-Dalsl. köp-m:förb., befullm. i Sv:es köpm:förb., ordf. i Åmåls bef :utb :fören., ordf. i Werml. Enisk. Bank A-B plats styr. Presid. i Åmåls Rotarykl. Hoibbies: friluftsliv, ’Småbruk.
translated: Canada, Japan, China, and India 21-23. Captain in the Värmland Regiment, reserved 46. Owner of the wholesale firm F.E. Karlström in Amål, as well as a small business in Åmål, Säffle, and Årjäng. Member of the city council (conservative) since 1937, vice chairman of the preparedness committee, and member of several other committees. Chairman of Åmåls Merchants Association, vice chairman of the Värmland-Dalarna Merchants Association, representative of the Swedish Merchants Association, chairman of Åmåls Education Association, chairman of Wermland Enisk Bank AB, board member. President of Åmåls Rotary Club. Hobbies: outdoor life and small-scale farming.
